<h1>Our Story</h1>
<p>Talksome was started in late 2016 with the goal of countering the problem of echo chambers -- or "<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B8ofWFx525s">filter bubbles</a>" -- in social media (click that link, it's good). This problem occurs when social networks strictly curate content that users are most likely to agree with and enjoy. These systems can decrease a user's tolerance other points of view and hide important information. And they're everywhere.</p>
<p>Talksome is committed to not unfairly targeting users with content they're most likely to enjoy at the expense of a balanced media diet.</p>
<p>Our goal isn't to make a profit, but like any website, we still have expenses. If you'd like to help us continue to run without ads and other such content, please help us out by donating!</p>
